<h1>Examples</h1>

<p class="l-ui-utility--mt-md">
  Browse the examples in the navigation to see <code>layered-resource-rails</code> in action.
</p>

<h2 class="l-ui-utility--mt-xl">Posts</h2>
<p class="l-ui-utility--mt-md">
  A standalone resource with full CRUD - create, read, update, and delete.
</p>

<h2 class="l-ui-utility--mt-xl">Users</h2>
<p class="l-ui-utility--mt-md">
  A read-only index with a posts count column that links to user-scoped posts.
  Also demonstrates restricted action sets:
</p>
<ul class="l-ui-list l-ui-utility--mt-md">
  <li><strong>Read Only</strong> - index only, no mutations</li>
  <li><strong>Deletable</strong> - index with destroy, no create or edit</li>
</ul>

<h2 class="l-ui-utility--mt-xl">Admin Posts</h2>
<p class="l-ui-utility--mt-md">
  A subclass (<code>AdminPostResource &lt; PostResource</code>) that inherits <code>model</code> and <code>search_fields</code>
  while overriding <code>columns</code> and <code>fields</code> - the inheritance pattern for variants like a separate admin area.
</p>
